content.problemStatement:
Variables which are of prime importance in your program can be considered as key variables.
with the help of key variables, we can check whether the program is working correctly or not. \
Program to check in the given array if there are even number of 3's multiple or an odd number of 3's multiple. 
```
#include 

int main() {
  int arr[13];
  for (int i = 0; i < 13; i++) {
    scanf("%d", &arr[i]);
  }
  int count = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < 13; i++) {
    if (arr[i] % 3 == 0) {
      count++;
    }
  }
  if (count % 2 == 0) {
    printf("even number of multiple of 3\n");
  } else {
    printf("odd number of multiples of 3\n");
  }

  return 0;
}
```
As in the above program we can see:-
- count tells the frequency of 3's multiple
- count help to find whether the frequency of 3's multiple is odd or even. \
So for this program, we can consider count as our key variable.

